    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is cooked, remove from the heat and break it apart into large, bite-sized pieces – this is your <strong>Mediterranean-style hake</strong></p><p>Remove the base of your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then wash under <strong>cold running water</strong> and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>lettuce leaves</strong> from the stem until you are left with a pile of leaves, then dress the<strong> lettuce leaves </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
